RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 65. Claiming Purse 8500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NOT WON A RACE IN 2023 OR WHICH HAVE NEVER WON FOUR RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $2,500.

CLAIM.OWNER: Martinez Alexis Silva and Marshall James

RACE.FOOTNOTES: YOUONLYLIVETWICE saved ground stalking the pace, angled out two-wide nearing the quarter pole, caught BELLS AND WHISTLES to take the lead nearing the sixteenth pole and won drawing clear. BELLS AND WHISTLES opened a clear lead shortly after the start, saved ground setting the pace, responded when challenged and while unable to resist the winner held on gamely for the place. SASSY EINSTEIN was unhurried early, came five-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. YELLEN saved ground while being allowed to settle in stride, angled out for the drive but lacked a rally. GOLD ROSE was forwardly placed for a half mile while two-wide and weakened. LAKER JET was prominently placed for three furlongs while three-wide, gave way badly and was pulled up nearing the wire and walked off following the race.

ENTRY.NAME: Yellen
ENTRY.COMMENT: settled, saved ground, angled out drive, lacked rally

ENTRY.NAME: Youonlylivetwice
ENTRY.OWNER: Durham Hillary and Rosales Racing F1
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked, saved ground, angled out 1/4. led 1/16. drawing clear

ENTRY.NAME: Bells and Whistles
ENTRY.COMMENT: clear early, set pace, responded, held gamely

ENTRY.NAME: Laker Jet
ENTRY.COMMENT: prominent, 3-wide, gave way, pulled up, walked off

CLAIM.OWNER: Elison Kenneth and Elison Vicky Jo

RACE.FOOTNOTES: STAND TO prompted the pace set by THE THIRD RING while racing two-wide, took the lead from that one leaving the quarter pole and then was fully extended to prevail narrowly. PISTOL POWER saved ground while being allowed to settle in stride, rallied three-wide into the stretch and finished strongly to just miss. WESTPHAL was unhurried early, came four-wide into the stretch and finished in a mild rally. THE THIRD RING saved ground setting the pace for a half mile and weakened. MARCH ON LINCH broke in the air to get away behind his field, raced three-wide on the turn and lacked a rally. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE START BUT AFTER VIEWING THE FILMS MADE NO CHANGE IN THE ORDER OF FINISH.

ENTRY.OWNER: Baze Lisa A and S and M Stable

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 3 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 74. Claiming Purse 9500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Non-winners Of A Race In 2023 Allowed 2 lbs. Claiming Price $5,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RAAJIN RIBBON dueled with DECIMATE for the lead to the stretch, shook that one off and gradually increased his advantage. OXBOW PARK was prominently placed while racing three-wide and finished in a mild rally. LARSEN BAY was unhurried early, came five-wide into the stretch and finished fast. ALTITUDE was allowed to settle in stride, moved up four-wide nearing the quarter pole but lacked a rally. DECIMATE dueled for the lead to the stretch from along the inside and weakened. STREET DEMAND saved ground while being reserved off the pace but failed to threaten.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 4 1M Dirt CR: 72. Maiden Claiming Purse 16500. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: MANGIA PANE saved ground setting the pace, repulsed a bid from ALL THE KING'S MEN nearing the quarter pole, opened clear nearing the eighth pole and maintained a safe advantage. BRANNIGAN saved ground while being reserved off the pace, moved forward along the inside in the stretch, angled out nearing the sixteenth pole and finished fast. WESTERBERG was allowed to settle in stride, came four-wide into the stretch and went evenly. MY DAD IS THIRSTY dropped back after stumbling at the start and was unable to recover the lost ground. CHARLIE'S MAN was unhurried early, came four-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: MARY WALKER dueled with MISS ACCELERATE for the lead from along the inside, shook that one off nearing the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. SCATALICIOUS was forwardly placed from the start, came three-wide into the stretch and finished well for second in a steady effort. MISS ACCELERATE dueled for the lead from along the outside, could not stay with the winner late but held on for the show. SHE SAID MY WAY saved ground while being unhurried, angled out for room nearing the sixteenth pole and was gaining late. LASSIE CAT settled in the middle of the field, came three-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. I AM YOURS was unhurried early, came five-wide into the stretch and failed to threaten. LUCINDA RELLA prompted the issue while racing three-wide but lacked a response. SIGNATURE COLORS was close up early racing along the inside and gave way after three furlongs.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ROYAL CANDY vied with SPARKS FLYIN for the lead from along the outside, shook that one off nearing the eighth pole and gradually drew clear. SPARKS FLYIN dueled with the winner into the stretch, was no match for that one but was clearly second best. CASH'S CAT saved ground chased the leaders, angled out for the drive and while unable to threaten the top two finished willingly for the show. CRAWLINGBACKTOYOU was allowed to settle in stride, came three-wide into the stretch but lacked a rally. GOOD DANNY broke out sharply then dropped well back and failed to menace.
